<div class="text install">
    <h1>Installation</h1>
    
    <strong>Requirements</strong>
    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>HTTP Server. For example: Apache. mod_rewrite is preferred, but by no means required.</li>
            <li>PHP 5.2.8 or greater.</li>
            <li>PDO extensions</li>
        </ul>
    </p>
    <strong>Download CakeCMS</strong>
    <div class="code">
        Visit the main website http://www.cakecms.com.br and follow the “Download” link.
    </div>
    <p>OR</p>
    <div class="code">
        git clone git://github.com/cakephp/cakephp.git
    </div>
    <p></p>
    <strong>Permissions</strong>
    <p>
        <div class="code">app/tmp</div>
        <div class="code">app/webroot/files/</div>
    </p>
    <strong>Define Diretory</strong>
    <p>The diretory default is /. If your aplication isseted in directory: /mysite/ <i>ex:www.example.com/mysite/</i>. Edit files: 
        <div class="code">
            app/webroot/js/admin/ckeditor/ckfinder/config.php | line: 67 '/app/webroot/files/uploads/' FOR '/mysite/cakecms/app/webroot/files/uploads/'
        </div>
    </p>
    <strong>Database</strong>
    <p>
        <div class="code">
            Import file app/cakecms.sql in database Mysql
        </div>
        <div class="code">
            Set data in file app/Config/database.php <br /><br />
            <i>
            public $default = array(<br />
                    'datasource' => 'Database/Mysql',<br />
                    'persistent' => false,<br />
                    'host' => 'localhost',<br />
                    'login' => 'root',<br />
                    'password' => '1234',<br />
                    'database' => 'cakecms',<br />
                    'prefix' => '',<br />
                    //'encoding' => 'utf8',<br />
            );<br />
            </i>
        </div>
    </p>
    <strong>Finishing</strong>
    <p>
        The developers contain special permissions in painel controll
        <div class="code">
            Acess admin: www.example.com/admin/ <br />
            Username: dev<br />
            password: cakecms<br />
        </div>
    </p>
     <p>
        The user
        <div class="code">
            Acess admin: www.example.com/admin/ <br />
            Username: admin<br />
            password: cakecms<br />
        </div>
    </p>
</div>
